    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": false,
    "title": "doc: clarify that -maxmempool minimum is derived from cluster size limit",
    "user": {
      "login": "fernandguil",
      "id": 39845628,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODQ1NjI4",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39845628?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/fernandguil",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fernandguil/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "`doc/reduce-memory.md` states that the minimum value for `-maxmempool` is a fixed `5`. This is no longer accurate: the minimum is computed dynamically from the mempool's cluster size limit.\n\nIn [`src/txmempool.cpp`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/txmempool.cpp):\n\n```cpp\nint64_t cluster_limit_bytes = opts.limits.cluster_size_vbytes * 40;\nif (opts.max_size_bytes < 0 || (opts.max_size_bytes > 0 && opts.max_size_bytes < cluster_limit_bytes)) {\n    error = strprintf(_(\"-maxmempool must be at least %d MB\"), std::ceil(cluster_limit_bytes / 1'000'000.0));\n}\n```\n\nWith the default cluster size limit (`DEFAULT_CLUSTER_SIZE_LIMIT_KVB = 101`, i.e. 101,000 vbytes), this works out to `101,000 * 40 = 4.04 MB`, rounded up to `5 MB` — so the documented `5` is correct only by coincidence of the current defaults.\n\nThis updates the wording to describe the actual behavior (derived from the cluster size limit, 5 MB by default) and mentions the `-maxmempool must be at least N MB` startup error a user will see if they set it too low.",
